what is z-index?
z-index determine The stack order of the element. it's default value is 0. and heighest z index element will apper on the top.
z index property can use with position relative absolute only.


gird-template-area?
grid-template-area is a shorthand property of gird-template-rows and grid-template-columns. and in this property we can specify the colums and rows and its height and width.
The grid-template-areas property specifies areas within the grid layout. You can name grid items by using the grid-area property, and then reference to the name in the grid-template-area.


Cascading in css?
Cascading refers to the process by which styles are applied to HTML elements. It involves a set of rules that tells how conflicting styles are resolved.










